{{engname|古奇建築|Googie architecture}}是一種現代建築的形式，屬於[[未來主義建築|未來主義建築]]的一種，受到汽車文化、[[噴射機|噴射機]]、[[太空時代|太空時代]]和[[核子時代|核子時代]]的影響<ref>{{cite news |last=Friedlander |first=Whitney |date=2008-05-18 |title=Go on a SoCal hunt for Googie architecture |agency=[[洛杉磯時報|Los Angeles Times]] |work=Baltimore Sun |accessdate=2009-02-11 |language= |quote=It was the 1950s. America was a superpower, and the Los Angeles area was a center of it. The space race was on. A car culture was emerging. So were millions of postwar babies. Businesses needed ways to get families out of their automobiles and into coffee shops, bowling alleys, gas stations and motels. They needed bright signs and designs showing that the future was now. They needed color and new ideas. They needed Googie. |url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/travel/la-trw-googie18-2008may18,0,7267506.story?page=1 |archive-date=2014-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106190555/http://www.baltimoresun.com/travel/la-trw-googie18-2008may18,0,7267506.story?page=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==歷史==
古奇建築在1940年代晚期起源於[[美國|美國]][[南加州|南加州]]，並延續至1960年代中期，在[[汽車旅館|汽車旅館]]、[[咖啡店|咖啡店]]和[[加油站|加油站]]建築中十分流行。古奇風格隨後成為[[世纪中期现代主义|世纪中期现代主义]]的一部份，其中的設計要素反映了當時在美國流行的「populuxe」美學<ref name="StagerCarver2006">{{cite book|last1=Stager|first1=Claudette|last2=Carver|first2=Martha|title=Looking Beyond the Highway: Dixie Roads and Culture|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=VkYQT_1pO4cC&pg=PA158|accessdate=2013-08-09|year=2006|publisher=Univ. of Tennessee Press|isbn=978-1-57233-467-0|page=158}}</ref><ref name="CotterYoung2004">{{cite book|last1=Cotter|first1=Bill|last2=Young|first2=Bill|title=The 1964-1965 New York World's Fair|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=mfbPbQmG9mQC&pg=PA51|accessdate=2013-08-09|year=2004|publisher=Arcadia Publishing|isbn=978-0-7385-3606-4|page=51|chapter=Populuxe and Pop Art}}</ref>，[[埃罗·沙里宁|埃罗·沙里宁]]的{{link-en|TWA飛行中心|TWA Flight Center}}即為一例。

古奇的英文（'''Googie'''）原名來自一間現已歇業的[[西好萊塢|西好萊塢]]咖啡店<ref name=latimes>{{cite news |first=Valerie J. |last=Nelson |title=Eldon Davis dies at 94; architect designed 'Googie' coffee shops |url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/news/arts/la-me-eldon-davis-20110426,0,5591348.story?track=rss |work=[[洛杉磯時報|Los Angeles Times]] |publisher= |date=2011-04-26 |accessdate=2011-05-15 |archive-date=2019-12-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210060515/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/news/arts/la-me-eldon-davis-20110426,0,5591348.story?track=rss |dead-url=no }}</ref>，由[[約翰·洛特納|約翰·洛特納]]（John Lautner）設計<ref>[http://www.archdaily.com/tag/john-lautner/ John Lautner] {{Wayback|url=http://www.archdaily.com/tag/john-lautner/ |date=20191204234025 }} Why Do Bad Guys Always Get The Best Houses? by Rory Stott ArchDaily</ref>。古奇建築的近似風格有時又稱作「Doo Wop」<ref>''[http://books.google.com/books?id=KdFQ8_csr9QC Doo Wop Motels: Architectural Treasures of The Wildwoods]'' by Kirk Hastings 2007, p.2</ref>。

==特徵==
古奇建築風格的特徵包括向上傾斜的屋頂、曲線的幾何形狀，以及大膽採用[[玻璃|玻璃]]、[[鋼鐵|鋼鐵]]和[[霓虹燈|霓虹燈]]。太空時代中象徵動作的設計元素也出現在古奇建築中，包括[[回力镖|回力镖]]、[[飛碟|飛碟]]、[[原子|原子]]和[[抛物线|抛物线]]，以及其他自由形態的要素，例如「柔和」的[[平行四边形|平行四边形]]等。這些設計風格要素反映了美國社會對太空時代的著迷，以及市場上對未來主義設計的重視與強調。

與1930年代的[[装饰风艺术|装饰风艺术]]相同，古奇風格隨著時間的經過逐漸變得不受重視，許多此一風格的建築也被拆除。而其中保存下來的包括一間{{link-en|最古老的麥當勞餐廳|Oldest McDonald's restaurant}}（位於[[加州|加州]][[唐尼_(加利福尼亞州)|唐尼市]]），已在1983年被列入美國[[國家史蹟名錄|國家史蹟名錄]]。

